metadata.description:
In the vast expanse of the galaxy,
A space pirate roams free,
His spirit wild and untamed,
A fierce warrior, unafraid.

With each planet he visits,
His thirst for adventure persists,
Searching for treasure and glory,
A story to tell in each new territory.

But beneath his pirate bravado,
Lies a longing for something more,
A yearning for true freedom,
To be unshackled and explore.

So he sets his sights on the stars,
And flies his ship far and wide,
Through asteroid fields and black holes,
In search of the freedom he desires.

For the space pirate knows deep inside,
That true freedom cannot be bought,
It's a feeling that comes from within,
A journey that cannot be taught.

And so he continues his quest,
To find the freedom that he seeks,
A quest that may never end,
But one that he knows is worth the leap.
